com.avaya.ic.sdk
Interface TranscriptLine

public interface TranscriptLine

Represents a message sent into the chat room, and reflects the displayable elements of a chat transcript. TranscriptLine messages can be simple text messages entered by a participant, a system broadcast message, or a URL pushed by a particular participant. TranscriptLine has properties that provide additional information related to the message, such as the originator of the call (whether agent, caller, system or unknown), or the type of message (whether text or url). When an agent receives a message sent into the chat room, the Client SDK creates a TranscriptLine object. The Client SDK provides the TranscriptLine object to the consumer through the TRANSCRIPT_LINE_ADDED event of TranscriptDocument.
